      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"3. CROWN KNOTT debuts for Charlie Appleby. The Lope De Vega gelding out of Lover's Knot makes obvious appeal on paper for a stable who enjoy much success at this meeting. Bold showing expected and market support would be significant. 7. PORTCULLIS is a well bred Frankel colt from G1 winner Castle Lady. Profiles as a major player first time out. 8. SANTUSHTI represents the Gosden yard and as a Dubawi newcomer she commands plenty of respect. Any confidence behind him would be notable. 6. NORTH BEACH is a New Bay colt from the Andrew Balding yard. Enough in the pedigree suggests he can make an immediate impact.\",\"runners\":[3,7,8,6],\"exclusive\":false}",
